long_desc.thetext:
Safari 4/PC + IE8:

qx.ui.embed.Iframe: The property overflow has no effect when it is set to "hidden".

FF3.6: shows no scrollbars if overflow is set to ["hidden", "hidden"], but Safari 4 and IE 8 do.

See the follwing example from the "playground" application:

var iframe = new qx.ui.embed.Iframe("http://web.de");
iframe .set({
  width : 300,
  height: 250,
  overflow : ["hidden", "hidden"]
});

// Document is the application root
var doc = this.getRoot();

// Add button to document at fixed coordinates
doc.add(iframe ,
{
  left : 100,
  top  : 50
});

The overflow has only an effect on FF, all other browsers ignore it.

A workaround until the bug is not fix is using the "scrolling" attribute:
iframe.getContentElement().setAttribute("scrolling", "no");
